HEADWORD: Cuppy
<hw>Cup"py</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Hollow;
cuplike; also, full of cups, or small depressions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Characterized by cup shakes; -- said of
timber.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cupreous</ent>⟦br⟧
